  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Today, the aqua feed market consumes more than 50% of European animal feed made from insects and this is expected to increase in the coming years (Liland et al., 2021).",
    "Today insect proteins cannot be fed to poultry in European Union as legislation passed after the BSE (bovine spongiform encephalopathy) crisis in the late 1990s prevents processed animal proteins from being fed to livestock.",
    "Only fishmeal may be used and yet, over 90% of EU insect feed producers see poultry feed as a 'promising opportunity' (IPIFF, 2018).",
    "Dörper et al. (2021) concluded that partial replacement of soybean meal by larvae of BSF or housefly in feed is beneficial for poultry.",
    "Chodova and Tumova (2020) reviewed a number of studies, and identified that insect meals can have a positive influence on growth of chickens without adverse impact on carcass and meat quality characteristics."
  ],
